# ChinaTravel — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Identity
This is **CTS Tours** — a luxury China tour operator website for New Zealand travellers.
- Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Supabase + Resend
- Live site: https://chinatravel-zloe.onrender.com
- Repo: https://github.com/bigbigraydeng-maker/chinatravel.git
- Deploy: Render (auto-deploys on push to `main`)

---

## Architecture

### Routing
```
src/app/
├── page.tsx                          # Homepage
├── layout.tsx                        # Root layout (Navbar + Footer)
├── sitemap.ts                        # Auto-generates /sitemap.xml
├── robots.ts                         # Auto-generates /robots.txt
├── china-tours/page.tsx              # Commercial hub
├── [destination]-tours/page.tsx      # 7 destination hubs (beijing, xian, etc.)
├── [destination]-travel-guide/       # 21 destination guides (Phase 2)
│   └── page.tsx
├── best-time-to-visit-china/         # Seasonal SEO page
├── china-visa-guide-for-new-zealanders/
├── china-tours-from-new-zealand/
├── china-tours-from-auckland/
├── tours/
│   └── [destination]/[tier]/[tour]/  # Dynamic tour detail pages
│       └── print/                    # Print-friendly itinerary
├── api/
│   ├── send-itinerary/route.ts       # Email itinerary (Resend)
│   └── tour-enquiry/route.ts         # Tour enquiry form
└── tailor-made/page.tsx              # Custom trip inquiry
```

### Key Data Files
```
src/lib/data/
├── tours.ts          # All tour products (22+ tours, destinations, tiers)
├── guides.ts         # All 21 destination guide data (2,500+ lines)
└── blog.ts           # Blog articles
```

### Key Components
```
src/components/
├── seo/
│   ├── DestinationGuide.tsx    # Template for all 21 guide pages (two-column layout)
│   └── HubHero.tsx             # Hero with Next.js Image for guide/hub pages
├── tours/
│   ├── TourHero.tsx            # Tour detail hero
│   ├── TourItinerary.tsx       # Day-by-day itinerary
│   └── TourGallery.tsx         # Image gallery
├── Hero.tsx                    # Homepage hero (Next.js Image)
├── TourTierCard.tsx            # Product card (Signature/Discovery/Stopover)
├── SchemaMarkup.tsx            # JSON-LD schema injector
└── Navbar.tsx / Footer.tsx
```

---

## Data Access Patterns

### Tours
```typescript
import { tours, getTourBySlug, destinations } from '@/lib/data/tours';

// Get a specific tour
const tour = getTourBySlug('beijing', 'stopover', 'beijing');

// All China tours
const chinaTours = tours.filter(t => t.destination === 'china');
```

### Guides
```typescript
import { getGuideBySlug, getGuidesByParent } from '@/lib/data/guides';

const guide = getGuideBySlug('beijing-travel-guide');
const yunnanSubGuides = getGuidesByParent('yunnan');
```

---

## SEO Requirements — CRITICAL

Every page MUST have:

### 1. Metadata (`generateMetadata` preferred, static `metadata` acceptable)
```typescript
export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    title: 'Specific Page Title | CTS Tours',  // 50-60 chars
    description: 'Unique description per page...',  // 140-160 chars
    keywords: ['keyword1', 'keyword2'],
    openGraph: {
      type: 'article',
      url: `https://chinatravel-zloe.onrender.com/${slug}`,
      title: '...',
      description: '...',
      images: [{ url: `https://chinatravel-zloe.onrender.com${heroImage}`, width: 1200, height: 630 }],
    },
    alternates: { canonical: `https://chinatravel-zloe.onrender.com/${slug}` },
    robots: { index: true, follow: true },
  };
}
```

### 2. Schema Markup — Pass to `<SchemaMarkup data={schema} />`
```typescript
// All guide pages use 3 schema types:
const schema = [
  { '@type': 'Article', headline: ..., datePublished: ..., author: ... },
  { '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [...] },
  { '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: guide.faqs.map(...) },
];
```

### 3. Never repeat titles/descriptions across pages
All 21 guide pages use `guide.metaTitle` and `guide.metaDescription` from `guides.ts`.

